---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Delete Articles" description="Tailnet-only wiki article deletion" wide>
  <p class="page-eyebrow">Tailnet admin</p>
  <h1>Delete wiki articles</h1>
  <p class="lead">
    This delete tool lives inside the Astro site, but the controls only appear when this browser can reach Tony's Tailnet-only admin API.
  </p>

  <section class="admin-panel no-print" id="wiki-delete-admin">
    <p><strong>Status:</strong> <span data-status>Checking Tailnet access…</span></p>

    <div data-locked>
      <p>
        Article deletion is hidden unless this browser can reach Tony's Tailnet-only admin API.
        Connect this device to Tailscale, then reload.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div data-tailnet-only hidden>
      <p>
        Tailnet verified. Deletes are soft-deleted locally, validated, built, committed,
        pushed to GitHub <code>main</code>, and then removed from Vercel after redeploy.
      </p>
      <label for="wiki-delete-filter">Filter articles</label>
      <input
        id="wiki-delete-filter"
        data-filter
        type="search"
        placeholder="Filter by title, slug, or path"
        style="width: 100%; padding: .7rem; margin: .35rem 0 1rem;"
      />
      <div data-list></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Security model</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>The delete UI is part of the Astro site.</li>
      <li>The controls remain hidden until this browser reaches the Tailnet-only API.</li>
      <li>The admin API runs on Alienware loopback and is exposed through Tailscale Serve HTTPS.</li>
      <li>Only Markdown files in <code>src/content/ideas/</code> can be deleted.</li>
      <li>Deleted files move to external recovery trash at <code>/home/rootadmin/weekly-review-wiki-trash/</code>.</li>
      <li>Successful deletes validate, build, commit, push to <code>main</code>, and rely on Vercel redeploy.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <script is:inline src="/assets/wiki-delete-admin.js"></script>
</BaseLayout>
